# How does the number of runs scored vary with the over number?

ipl.groupby('over')['total_runs'].sum().plot(kind='line',color='blue')
plt.title('Runs scored in each over')
plt.xlabel('Overs',fontweight="bold")
plt.ylabel('Total Runs',fontweight="bold")
plt.show()

# Are there any notable trends in the distribution of runs scored by batting teams across innings?

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
runs_inn=ipl.groupby(['inning','batting_team'])['total_runs'].sum().reset_index()

sns.scatterplot(data=runs_inn,x='inning',y='total_runs',hue='batting_team')
plt.title('Distribution of runs scored by Batting Teams across innings')
plt.xlabel('Innings',fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Total Runs Scored',fontweight='bold')
plt.show()

In [549]:
# Which bowler has the highest economy rate?

eco_rate= ipl.groupby('bowler').agg({'total_runs': 'sum', 'over': 'nunique', 'ball': 'max'})
eco_rate['total_overs'] = eco_rate['over'] + eco_rate['ball'] / 6

eco_rate['economy_rate'] = eco_rate['total_runs'] / eco_rate['total_overs']
